theorem closure_interior_inter_eq_closure_interior_intersection
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (interior (A : Set X) ∩ interior B) =
      closure (interior (A ∩ B : Set X)) := by
  -- First, identify `interior A ∩ interior B` with `interior (A ∩ B)`.
  have hInt : interior (A : Set X) ∩ interior B =
      interior (A ∩ B : Set X) := by
    -- `interior_inter` gives the equality in the opposite direction.
    have h' : interior (A ∩ B : Set X) =
        interior (A : Set X) ∩ interior B :=
      interior_inter (A := A) (B := B)
    simpa using h'.symm
  -- Rewriting with `hInt` yields the desired equality of closures.
  simpa [hInt]

theorem interior_compl_closed {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA_closed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) :
    interior ((Aᶜ) : Set X) = Aᶜ := by
  simpa using hA_closed.isOpen_compl.interior_eq
